{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For example, claims about risk detection model accuracy were discussed at the International Association of Gaming Regulators annual conference (Percy, 2024), with examples including claims that models can exceed 80% accuracy (Sustainable Interaction, n.d.), 87% (Mindway AI, n.d.), and over 90% (Entain, 2022).",
    "While including such numbers is a positive step for corporate transparency, these claims are nearly impossible to evaluate without critical context for at least three reasons.",
    "First, a \"high accuracy\" claim can be misleading.",
    "For example, in a population where only 10% of individuals have a problem, a model could achieve 90% accuracy simply by identifying no one as at-risk.",
    "Second, these figures are not necessarily comparable."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For example, claims about risk detection model accuracy were discussed at the International Association of Gaming Regulators annual conference (Percy, 2024), with examples including claims that models can exceed 80% accuracy (Sustainable Interaction, n.d.), 87% (Mindway AI, n.d.), and over 90% (Entain, 2022)."
  ]
}